snippet.title: Dramatic crash footage: Ferry crashes onto shore in Turkey

localized.description:
Subscribe to ITN News: http://bit.ly/1bmWO8h
A ferry has made a dramatic final docking after crashing into land at speed in Turkey. Footage shows the Ostend Spirit heading to the shore, before scraping to a standstill between two boats. The vessel had been retired by its owners, and was coming to rest for the last time at the ship-breaking yard in Aliaga, Turkey, where it will later be taken apart. The ship, formerly known as The Pride of Calais, served as a channel ferry for P&O Ferries, travelling between Dover and Calais for 22 years until 2012. Report by Sophie Foster.
